19
00:02:00,033 --> 00:02:08,833
That question is, is the persistence of religion a temporary phenomenon that will eventually be replaced by science?

20
00:02:08,833 --> 00:02:11,200
Okay, let's begin with Rupert.

21
00:02:11,233 --> 00:02:19,500
Well, what makes religions different from mechanistic materialism, which is the usual belief system underlying atheism.

22
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:28,433
There are many kinds of atheism, but the common or garden atheists, the kind of Richard Dawkins type atheists, are usually mechanistic materialists.

23
00:02:28,466 --> 00:02:40,900
What makes all religions different is the belief that there are forms of consciousness that are higher than or more inclusive than human consciousness, that our consciousness is not the only kind there is.

24
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:51,166
I mean, most materialists would admit that some animals are conscious too, but otherwise they see the entire universe as made up of unconscious matter.

25
00:02:51,200 --> 00:03:12,366
And then consciousness somehow emerges in a very mysterious way inside material brains when they get big enough, and the light bulb of consciousness goes on, but consciousness doesn't actually do anything, it doesn't give us free will, it's nothing but the activity of our brains.

26
00:03:12,366 --> 00:03:21,133
That's the standard mechanistic materialist view, and of course when we die then the brain decays and all consciousness comes to an end.

27
00:03:21,166 --> 00:03:33,366
That worldview leads to the idea that God, gods, spirits, angels, etc., are nothing but fantasies inside human minds and therefore inside human brains.

28
00:03:33,366 --> 00:03:42,500
But this is just an assumption about the nature of consciousness, and in fact mechanistic materialism is extremely bad at explaining consciousness.

29
00:03:42,533 --> 00:03:52,033
The very existence of consciousness is an embarrassment, which is why it's called the hard problem in the philosophy of mind.

30
00:03:52,033 --> 00:03:56,833
So it's not as if mechanistic materialism has a brilliant theory of consciousness that explains it all.

31
00:03:56,866 --> 00:04:02,333
It doesn't have a theory at all, except to say it's nothing but brain activity.

32
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:11,833
On the other hand, when scientists actually look at the effects of religious and spiritual practices rather than approaching it in an ideological spirit,

33
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:18,900
then it turns out that religious and spiritual practices have measurable effects.

34
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:27,366
There have now been thousands of studies of the effects of spiritual and religious practices published in peer-reviewed journals.

35
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:33,933
