39
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:15,533
is that they on the whole get depressed, and of course depression is the endemic problem in industrial secular societies.

40
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:20,166
Millions and millions of people are on antidepressants.

41
00:05:20,166 --> 00:05:29,333
So, presumably this lack of religious and spiritual practice is bad for health, and that's why I think

42
00:05:29,866 --> 00:05:38,533
militant atheism should come with a health warning, because insofar as it puts people off their traditional religion and religious practices,

43
00:05:39,300 --> 00:05:48,500
and leaves very little in their stead except a belief in science, then it's likely to harm people.

44
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:50,700
Spiritual practices are not going away.

45
00:05:50,733 --> 00:05:58,733
On the contrary, they're increasing in their reach and in the number of people taking them up.

46
00:05:58,733 --> 00:06:02,633
So for me the question is not about the value of spiritual practices,

47
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:11,366
the question is whether spiritual practices will reconnect with religious traditions from which they originally came,

48
00:06:11,433 --> 00:06:20,000
whether religions will adopt more spiritual practices, because primarily it's about practice not about belief,

49
00:06:20,033 --> 00:06:32,600
and or whether we'll have large numbers of people who are spiritual but not religious, whose practices float in a kind of secular void, unrooted in spiritual in religious traditions.

50
00:06:33,366 --> 00:06:39,633
